<li><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=J0RX1mbhzAEC&amp;printsec=toc&amp;dq=bk7+optical+glass+construction&amp;source=gbs_summary_s&amp;cad=0#PRA1-PA58,M1" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=J0RX1mbhzAEC&amp;printsec=toc&amp;dq=bk7+optical+glass+construction&amp;source=gbs_summary_s&amp;cad=0#PRA1-PA58,M1" rel="nofollow">Book- The properties of optical glass</a></li>
<li><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=_T9dX14rz64C&amp;pg=PT415&amp;lpg=PT415&amp;dq=camera++optical+glass++composition&amp;source=web&amp;ots=YMMv0GjGDL&amp;sig=8VZXryxlUfcVq3nonFvrNWElkoI&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=book_result&amp;resnum=7&amp;ct=result" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=_T9dX14rz64C&amp;pg=PT415&amp;lpg=PT415&amp;dq=camera++optical+glass++composition&amp;source=web&amp;ots=YMMv0GjGDL&amp;sig=8VZXryxlUfcVq3nonFvrNWElkoI&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=book_result&amp;resnum=7&amp;ct=result" rel="nofollow">Handbook of Ceramics, Glasses, and Diamonds</a></li>
<li><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=KdYclkhSfTAC&amp;pg=PT49&amp;lpg=PT49&amp;dq=optical+glass+ingredients&amp;source=web&amp;ots=sLEkmvi05g&amp;sig=F6ERFbklTewIvFuKh30POTb0JG0&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=book_result&amp;resnum=7&amp;ct=result" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=KdYclkhSfTAC&amp;pg=PT49&amp;lpg=PT49&amp;dq=optical+glass+ingredients&amp;source=web&amp;ots=sLEkmvi05g&amp;sig=F6ERFbklTewIvFuKh30POTb0JG0&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=book_result&amp;resnum=7&amp;ct=result" rel="nofollow">Optical glass construction</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio4/history/inourtime/inourtime.shtml" class="external text" title="http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio4/history/inourtime/inourtime.shtml" rel="nofollow">History of Optics (audio mp3)</a> by Simon Schaffer, Professor in History and Philosophy of Science at the <a href="/wiki/University_of_Cambridge" title="University of Cambridge">University of Cambridge</a>, Jim Bennett, Director of the Museum of the History of Science at the <a href="/wiki/University_of_Oxford" title="University of Oxford">University of Oxford</a> and Emily Winterburn, Curator of Astronomy at the <a href="/wiki/National_Maritime_Museum" title="National Maritime Museum">National Maritime Museum</a> (recorded by the <a href="/wiki/BBC" title="BBC">BBC</a>).</li>
<li><a href="http://www.lightandmatter.com/html_books/5op/ch04/ch04.html" class="external text" title="http://www.lightandmatter.com/html_books/5op/ch04/ch04.html" rel="nofollow">a chapter from an online textbook on refraction and lenses</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.physnet.org/modules/pdfmodules/m223.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.physnet.org/modules/pdfmodules/m223.pdf" rel="nofollow"><i>Thin Spherical Lenses</i></a> on <a href="http://www.physnet.org" class="external text" title="http://www.physnet.org" rel="nofollow">Project PHYSNET</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.digitalartform.com/lenses.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.digitalartform.com/lenses.htm" rel="nofollow">Lens article at <i>digitalartform.com</i></a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.phy.ntnu.edu.tw/java/Lens/lens_e.html" class="external text" title="http://www.phy.ntnu.edu.tw/java/Lens/lens_e.html" rel="nofollow">Thin Lens Java applet</a></li>
<li><a href="http://home.comcast.net/~hebsed/enoch.htm" class="external text" title="http://home.comcast.net/~hebsed/enoch.htm" rel="nofollow">Article on Ancient Egyptian lenses</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www3.usal.es/%7Ehistologia/aplicacion/english/museum/microsco/micros01/micros01.htm" class="external text" title="http://www3.usal.es/%7Ehistologia/aplicacion/english/museum/microsco/micros01/micros01.htm" rel="nofollow">picture of the Ninive rock crystal lens</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.vias.org/simulations/simusoft_lenses.html" class="external text" title="http://www.vias.org/simulations/simusoft_lenses.html" rel="nofollow">Learning by Simulations</a> - Concave and Convex Lenses</li>
<li><a href="http://luminous-landscape.com/tutorials/resolution.shtml" class="external text" title="http://luminous-landscape.com/tutorials/resolution.shtml" rel="nofollow">Do Sensors “Outresolve” Lenses?</a>; on lens and sensor resolution interaction.</li>
</ul>
